quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  85,1,By the sky full of constellations
  85,2,and by the promised Day
  85,3,and by the witness and the witnessed
  85,4,cursed be the makers of the trench
  85,5,the fire full of fuel
  85,6,when they sat around it
  85,7,and were witnessing what they did to the believers
  85,8,"Their only grievance against them was that they believed in Allah, the All-Mighty, the Praiseworthy"
  85,9,"to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth, and Allah is Witness over all things"
  85,10,"Indeed, for those who tortured the believing men and women, then did not repent, there will be the punishment of Hell and the punishment of the burning fire"
  85,11,But those who believed and did righteous deeds will certainly have gardens under which rivers flow; that is the supreme triumph
  85,12,"Indeed, the punishment of your Lord is severe"
  85,13,"Indeed, it is He Who originates [the creation] then repeats it"
  85,14,"and He is the All-Forgiving, the Most Affectionate"
  85,15,the Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,He does whatever He wills
  85,17,Has there not come to you the story of the forces
  85,18,of Pharaoh and Thamūd
  85,19,But the disbelievers are in persistent denial
  85,20,although Allah encompasses them from all sides
  85,21,But this is a glorious Qur’an
  85,22,"[inscribed] in a Preserved Tablet"